#   ULOG tickets: append-log & store durability

Discrepancies in `dog/ULOG.*` вЂ” the append-only `<ts>\t<verb>\t<uri>` event log (worktree `.be` / store `wtlog`) and the `refs`/`.refs.idx` tip files built on it. Durability and crash-safety of these logs. Each entry is one ticket with its live state; it drops off once the ticket closes. The method is [Issues].

##  Active tickets

 -  [ULOG-001] вЂ” **LANDED `9cfa9639`.** Root cause: `be` *amplified* a torn ULOG into total loss вЂ” a NUL at byte 0 made `ulog_scan_log` read the log as empty, then `ULOGClose`в†’`FILETrimBook`в†’`ftruncate(0)` (`abc/FILE.c:945`) destroyed the surviving bytes (wtlog+refs are both ULOGs; `.keeper` packs are off this path, hence objects survived the 2026-06-09 incident). Fix: `ulog_scan_log` refuses a mid-content NUL with non-NUL bytes ahead (new `ULOGTORN`) and `ULOGOpenBooked` restores the original on-disk size on refusal вЂ” the torn log is left byte-for-byte for out-of-band repair, never zeroed. Regression `dog/test/ULOG.c` (torn-first-byte/torn-mid; fail pre-fix, pass post-fix). NB the *initial-NUL trigger* (ENOSPC / kill-mid-write / clone) was not pinned вЂ” H3 concurrent-race did NOT repro, H2 9p ruled out (all ext4). Follow-up candidates: clone of an empty/elided-refs store writes a 0-byte `refs` + `be get` HOME-escape; latent `O_TRUNC` seed at `sniff/SUBS.c:410/420`.

